ntations of 20-40 minutes, followed by a discussion round of 20-40 minutes, for a total of one hour per speaker.</p> <p>First Talk: Clean Architecture for Go Microservices (Max Wolter)</p> <p>Clean Architecture is a concept for the architecture of applications which separates the code into several layers according to whether they are specific to the application and/or specific to the business. Applying the approach to Go microservices leads to components that are easily testable, exchangeable and maintainable without touching the rest of the application code. This talk gives a brief overview of how to apply Clean Architecture to a Go application in practice.</p> <p>Second Talk: TBA</p> <p>(please don\'t hesitate to get in touch if you want to give a talk)</p> ','','',NULL),(27,2,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','https://www.meetup.com/Public-Speaking-Casemates-Toastmasters/events/237931981/','<p>Casemates is one of Luxembourg\'s English-speaking Toastmasters clubs - here you’ll find a supportive and friendly environment which will allow you to develop your communication skills, become a confident leader and have fun!</p> <p><br/>Each meeting is clearly structured with three parts: improvised speaking on various topics, prepared speeches by members, and an evaluation part where all the speakers receive feedback. Members are holding the various roles necessary for the organisation - a different one at each meeting. You can come as a guest and see how it works for yourself - we guarantee that you will feel welcomed and will have fun in our learn-by-doing environment!</p> ','','',NULL),(28,2,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','https://www.meetup.com/Meditation-Yoga-Saarbrucken-Birkenfeld-Idar-Oberstein/events/238189760/','<p>Tous les mardis et jeudis à 19h</p> <p>140 Av. Gaston Diderich L-1420 Luxembourg</p> <p>Info : (00352)[masked] ou gsm (00352)[masked]</p> <p>or (00352)[masked] (also english spoken)</p> <p><br/>\"Dans le silence au-delà des pensées, vous trouvez la paix intérieure.\"<br/><a href=\"https://www.sahajayoga.be/fr/shri-mataji.html\">Shri Mataji Nirmala Devi</a></p> <p><b>Faites l\'expérience!</b></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><a href=\"https://www.sahajayoga.be/fr/testimonials/celine.html\">\"La méditation donne véritablement un sens à ma vie, je me sens comme guidée vers ce qui est beau et juste.\"<br/></a><a href=\"https://www.sahajayoga.be/fr/testimonials/celine.html\">Celine, 39 ans,<br/>travailleur psycho-social</a></p> <p><a href=\"https://www.sahajayoga.be/fr/testimonials/celine.html\"><br/></a></p> <p><a href=\"https://www.sahajayoga.be/fr/luxembourg.html?lang=fr\" class=\"linkified\">https://www.sahajayoga.be/fr/luxembourg.html?lang=fr</a></p> <p>\n\n\nHello there! We\'d like to welcome you to our FREE weekly Sahaja Yoga meditation.</p> <p>With Sahaja Yoga Meditation we generally sit on chairs to achieve Yoga, effortlessly, spontaneously. As such no Asanas (exercises) are required, no mat or special clothing. We are all volunteers of a Charity organisation and have many years of experience in offering free Sahaja Yoga Meditation classes. The classes are designed to help those attending get into a genuine meditative state, which can be felt tangibly. It is quite effortless and spontaneous. The free classes feature introductory talks, video\'s, practical workshops and general question and answer opportunities, making them perfect for seekers trying to establish a state of yoga, and they are available throughout Luxembourg and  Germany.</p> <p>The idea is that you don\'t do yoga - you Achieve Yoga!</p> <p>Sahaja Yoga Meditation is a simple, time-honored technique. It helps those who enjoy it, reduce stress and increase wellness. It brings better focus and helps people become more centered and better balanced. Anyone can do it. Founded by Shri Mataji Nirmala Devi, Sahaja Yoga Meditation is a world wide movement for peace and self awakening.</p> <p>All the meetings and classes are free of any charge. Each week we go through simple meditation techniques, often with guided meditations to help reduce stress and achieve the peace of true meditation. We share tips on how to help stay in balance during the day and how to meditate at home. The meditation is based on connecting with the inner chakras (energy centres) and balancing the subtle body. The tradition and aims of meditation are explained which in essence is to be in the present with no mental activity or thoughts about the past or the future.</p> ','','',NULL),(29,2,NULL,'','2017-03-14 19:30:00','2017-03-14 21:30:00','','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourg-expats-and-repats/events/238214397/','','','',NULL),(30,2,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','https://www.meetup.com/Euro-Price-Action-Traders-Meetup/events/237845150/','<p>Illustration avec le pétrole brut :</p> <p><br/>Analyse: Quelles sont les données fondamentales actuelles influençant les cours du brut? Quels sont les niveaux pivots sur les graphes des prix, là où \"ça passe ou ça casse\"? Comment se comportent les prix à l\'énoncé de l\'inventaire américain pour la semaine écoulée ?</p> <p>Mise en pratique : En conclusion de cette analyse, une décision sera prise: acheter, vendre ou rester à l\'écart, selon que notre plan d\'action indique que les prix grimpent, baissent ou font du sur place par rapport aux niveaux pivots préalablement déterminés.</p> ','','',NULL),(31,2,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourg-expats-and-repats/events/236577716/','','','',NULL),(32,2,NULL,'','2017-03-15 19:00:00','2017-03-15 23:00:00','','https://www.meetup.com/Lesbian_in_Luxembourg/events/237677774/','','','',NULL),(33,2,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourg-Dart-Lang-Meetup/events/237781037/','<p><b>Agenda: </b></p> <p><b>1/ \"Angular Dart Overview\" presentation </b></p> <p><br/>- Level: Intermediate <br/>- Target: Web application developer <br/>- Speaker: Stéphane Este-Gracias <br/>- Duration: 60 min</p> <p><b>2/ \"Angular Dart\" workshop</b></p> <p>- Level: Intermediate <br/>- Target: Web application developer </p> <p><br/>- Duration: 30 min</p> <p><b>3/ Networking</b></p> <p><br/><b>Purpose: <br/></b><a href=\"https://www.dartlang.org/\">Dart</a> is a general-purpose programming language to build web, server, IoT and mobile applications. </p> <p><a href=\"https://webdev.dartlang.org/angular\">AngularDart</a> - also called Angular 2 for Dart or simply Angular - is a web app framework that focuses on productivity, performance, and stability. Hundreds of Google engineers use AngularDart to build the sophisticated, mission-critical apps that bring in much of Google’s revenue.</p> <p>Dart and AngularDart significantly increase the productivity of the developers.</p> <p><br/><b>Prerequisites:</b>  <br/><b>This meeting is about technologies within application development. </b>In order to participate to this meeting, it would be better to know at least one programming language in the scope of application development for Web or/and Mobile as Javascript, C#, Java...</p> ','','',NULL),(34,2,NULL,'','2017-03-15 19:00:00','2017-03-15 21:00:00','','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourg-expats-and-repats/events/238319113/','','','',NULL),(35,2,NULL,'','2017-03-15 20:00:00','2017-03-15 22:00:00','','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourg-Technical-and-Professional-Writing-Meetup/events/238138285/','<p>Let\'s meet up and have drinks at Rocas Cafe. Get to meet new people who have an interest or background in writing if you missed our first meetup. This is a casual and all are welcome. No writing is going to happen here. Just fun:)</p> ','','',NULL),(36,2,NULL,'','2017-03-16 10:00:00','2017-03-16 12:00:00','','https://www.meetup.com/Luxmama-Club-ParentPrep-asbl/events/236502164/','<p><img src=\"http://photos3.meetupstatic.com/photos/event/2/5/4/600_457140596.jpeg\" /></p> <p>Bellies &amp; Booties is a monthly Luxmama Club event blending the perfect mix of learning and fun for Expecting and New Parents!</p> <p>Come and hang with us, mingle and enjoy our interesting themes/guests and quite often give-aways…plus you get access to all our partner discounts... AND you can have a chat with our Maternity &amp; Parenting Professionals: Birth Doula, Child-birth Educator, Perinatal Educator/Coach, Holistic Pregnancy &amp; Child Sleep Coach</p> <p>No bookings required, just rock up!</p> <p>Please note, we have changed the venue to Cathy Goedert Patisserie! After the event, you are very welcome to stay with us for lunch!</p> <p>Also, Bellies and Booties will be now taking place on THURSDAY.</p> <p>Ticket: 15 Euro including refreshment and snack/ 10 Euro without</p> <p>For more info: <a href=\"http://www.luxmamaclub.com/\"><a href=\"http://www.luxmamaclub.com/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.luxmamaclub.com/</a></a></p> <p><a href=\"http://www.luxmamaclub.com/belliesandbootiesprogram\"><a href=\"http://www.luxmamaclub.com/belliesandbootiesprogram\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.luxmamaclub.com/belliesandbootiesprogram</a></a></p> <p>For Bellies &amp; Booties memories: <a href=\"http://www.luxmamaclub.com/belliesandbootiesmemories\"><a href=\"http://www.luxmamaclub.com/belliesandbootiesmemories\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.luxmamaclub.com/belliesandbootiesmemories</a></a></p> ','','',NULL),(37,2,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourg-Technical-and-Professional-Writing-Meetup/events/238138463/','<p>Just a meetup for writers sitting around, doing what they do. Writing. Eating. Drinking. Join me on<br/>Thursday evenings at Konrad Cafe to Shut Up &amp; Write! ... nested close to the city center. The meetings will be consistent depending on the number who join and availablity. Come write in a supportive, encouraging environment while supporting a friendly, locally owned business with a sense of community. Konrad has free wi-fi, delicious deli delights, and affordable, quality wine, beer and coffee! </p> <p>\n\n\nThe meet up officially starts at 5 with brief introductions and chit-chat, feel free to come even earlier if you like to order food/drinks. At 5:15 we put in our earbuds, set the alarm for 6:15 and start writing! When the time\'s up we take a short break to greet any late arrivals, order more food/drink and chat before we start writing again. We wrap up around 7:15 when people are free to stay, work, eat/drink or chat until 7:30, when the organizer leaves. </p> <p>I realize getting here by 5 can be a challenge, and I am happy to have late-comers or drop-ins, but if this is you, please be respectful of others who are working and save introductions until we take a break, unless I am the only one there:) I\'ll be thrilled to greet you then!</p> <p>Do you have a blog or website that is being neglected? Dreaming of getting your business or site off the ground but have a hard time carving out the time or space for yourself? Need a creative boost and work better in the evenings? It isn\'t easy to sit down and write on a consistent basis on a project or passion that you love when you work full-time or have many other obligations. Here is your chance.</p> <p>“Writing is the only thing that, when I do it, I don\'t feel I should be doing something else.“ - Gloria Steinem</p> ','','',NULL),(38,2,NULL,'','2017-03-16 18:00:00','2017-03-16 21:00:00','','https://www.meetup.com/FinTech-Luxembourg/events/237719405/','<p><b>Silicon Luxembourg</b> and the <b>Khube</b> are happy to organize a <i>speed dating</i> event between startups and banks.</p> <p><b>10 entrepreneurs will have the chance to “speed date” and pitch to banks’ executives</b> in the ambient surroundings of a wine bar in Luxembourg city.</p> <p>Are you a startup? Are your clients in the banking industry? Just fill out the 1-pager (request it by email, please) and send along a presentation about your company to <a href=\"mailto:[masked]\">[masked]</a> before February 27. The 10 selected startups will be notified by March 2.</p> <p><b>Agenda:</b></p> <p>6:00 – 6:30 pm: Welcome and Registration<br/>6:30 – 6:50 pm: Opening Remarks by Alexandre Rochegude, Partner at KPMG Luxembourg and Charles-Louis Machuron, Founder of Silicon Luxembourg<br/>6:50 – 7:30 pm: Pitching sessions<br/>7:30 – 8:30 pm: Networking Dinner</p> ','','',NULL),(39,2,NULL,'','2017-03-16 18:00:00','2017-03-16 20:30:00','','https://www.meetup.com/JEDI-Jeudi-Digital/events/238236867/','<p>Face à une crise économique qui tarde à se résorber, l’innovation semble constituer une réponse particulièrement pertinente aux problématiques sociales qui en découlent : logement, emploi, accès à l’éducation, à la santé. Souvent perçue via sa composante technologique, l’innovation peut, et doit, s’assigner pour mission de servir l’intérêt général. Dans ce contexte, les villes se mobilisent de plus en plus pour répondre aux besoins spécifiques des territoires en s’appuyant sur celles et ceux qui les font vivre. Si elles ont compris que l’innovation territoriale était une réelle aubaine pour leur développement et la création d’une nouvelle dynamique, reste encore à savoir comment l’encourager et renouveler ses pratiques. La ville de Metz se situe à l’avant-poste de cette tendance et semble avoir compris la nécessité de co-créer avec l’ensemble des parties prenantes du territoire. En ce sens, et dans le cadre de sa démarche Impact Metz, elle a mis a contribution le Mouvement UP à travers la mise en place du tout premier réseau social territorial messin, dédié aux initiatives citoyennes locales qui ont du sens : UP Metz. Pour découvrir et construire ensemble ce nouvel outil, nous vous invitons à la grande soirée de lancement d\'UP Metz, le jeudi 16 mars prochain. Inscription obligatoire sur : <a href=\"http://up-conferences.fr/evenement/soiree-lancement-up-metz-quand-innovation-rencontre-territoires\" class=\"linkified\">http://up-conferences.fr/evenement/soiree-lancement-up-metz-quand-innovation-rencontre-territoires</a></p> ','','',NULL),(40,2,NULL,'','2017-03-16 18:00:00','2017-03-16 20:00:00','','https://www.meetup.com/CoderDojoLu/events/238320838/','<p>This is the weekly CoderDojo in Luxembourg at the <a href=\"https://level2.lu/\">Level2</a> hackerspace.</p> <p>It is intended for 12-18 year olds, but younger kids are welcome too.</p> <p>The dojo is a the perfect place for young people to learn about technology and programming in particular, to work on their own ideas and collaborate on creative projects.</p> <p>Bringing your personal laptop is a good idea, but you can also borrow one from our pool. You may also want to bring a healthy snack to keep going, free water is at your disposal.</p> <p>Perhaps most importantly: Bring your curiosity to think outside of the box, respect everyone unconditionally and be happy to be with like minded people.</p> <p>A parent has to be present at the start and end of each session. If you are 12 or under, your parent should stay with you during the session.</p> <p>Mir schwätze Lëtzebuergesch, wir sprechen Deutsch, nous parlons français, we speak English and we will adapt to the variety of the group.</p> <p><b>FAQs</b></p> <p><b>Are there any ID requirements or an age limit?</b><br/>The idea of CoderDojo is to enable 12-18 year olds to get into programming and technology. We are not strict on age. but for younger kids (7-11) you may first want to get in touch with <a href=\"http://www.codeclub.lu/\">Code Club Luxembourg</a> to see where elementary school courses take place.<br/>Age is only given as an indication, so when in doubt please drop by!</p> <p><b>What are my transport/parking options?</b><br/>There is a plethora of parking spaces around the Bonnevoie area and public transport is running in 10 minute intervals. <a href=\"https://wiki.hackerspace.lu/wiki/Location\">Click here for more details</a></p> <p><b>What can/can\'t I bring to the dojo?</b><br/>Any form of intolerance or technology aversion should be left outside. Please bring your curiosity, your motivation and your laptop if possible. We do have some spare laptops around but coding on your own machine is always better.</p> <p><b>Where can I contact the organizer with any questions?</b><br/>&lt;a&gt;[masked]&lt;/a&gt;</p> ','','',NULL),(41,2,NULL,'','2017-03-16 18:15:00','2017-03-16 20:30:00','','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourg-Ultimate-Frisbee/events/238107487/','<p>Come out (or indoors!) for Thursday evening practices with the Luxembourg Ultimate frisbee team.  When indoor (Winter), we meet at Lycee Aline Mayrisch: Parallel to the Blvd Pierre Dupond is a red running track, go up the stairs and you will see the indoor gym. If outdoor (Spring/Summer/Fall), we meet either at Michel Lucius in Limpertsberg or the ISL artificial turf field (International School Lux in Hollerich), right behind the same red track, in the ISL campus. Meetup will be updated with the venue.</p> <p><br/>Practices are open to All, free while you discover the game and team, and Beginners are welcome ! We stretch and warm up, do drills, work strategy and play games. Even if only a few sign up through Meetup, practices still take place ! Send Thierry a mail through Meetup or Check our website for contact details ! More information here:  <a href=\"http://www.ultimate-delux.org/Main_Page#Practice\"><a href=\"http://www.ultimatedelux.org/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.ultimatedelux.org/</a></a></p> ','','',NULL),(42,2,NULL,'','2017-03-16 18:30:00','2017-03-16 20:30:00','','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourg-Wine-Tasting-Meetup/events/238078969/','<p>This is not realy a meetup kind of event, but never the less a great chance to get to such a tasting. Mr Francois Wilhelm from Domaine Trimbach and Mr Antoine Clasen will be holding a presentation on their wines at the Cercle Munster. You will get the chance to go to the most exclusive Private members Club in Luxembourg and taste some fantastic wines and tapas. To wear a tie is mandatory for men. The Cost for this Event is 30€ pp.(payment up front) Please email me directly to be added to the guest list.</p> ','','',NULL),(43,2,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourg-Software-Testing/events/237821876/','<p>Topic and place under review.</p> ','','',NULL),(44,2,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','https://www.meetup.com/Saarland-Softwarequalitatssicherung-Testautomatisierung/events/238037920/','<p>In diesem Meetup erhalten wir Einblick in die Qualitätssicherung eines der größten Online-Versicherer Deutschlands.Der Referent, Björn Scherer, arbeitet bei eCosmos, der Online-Unit von CosmosDirekt, und erzählt uns in seinem Vortrag von den Herausforderungen der Testautomatisierung mit starkem Frontend-Fokus im Rahmen einer Mehrschicht-Architektur und wie man diesen bei CosmosDirekt begegnet.</p> <p><br/>Ein Auszug aus den behandelten Fragen:</p> <p><br/>Zur Automatisierung von browserbasierten Anwendungen ist Selenium quasi Markt-Standard. Auch wir nutzen es für unser Kunden-Frontend. Aber in unseren cross-funktionalen, agilen Teams arbeiten nicht nur Entwickler, sondern auch fachlich orientierten Kollegen, für die die reine WebDriver-API teilweise zu technisch ist. </p> <p>=&gt; Wie schaffen wir es eine gemeinsame Sprache zu schaffen?</p> <p>=&gt; Wie gelingt uns das Mapping zwischen fachlich formulierten Test-Schritten und der technischen Implementierung?</p> <p>=&gt; Was hilft uns bei der Strukturierung und Organisation großer Mengen an Testfällen?</p> <p>Auch mit starkem Fokus auf das Kunden-Frontend, geht nichts ohne Backend: Sei es zur Schaffung von Test-Voraussetzungen / Testdaten, oder zum Setzen erweiterter Prüfpunkte.</p> <p>=&gt; Wie schaffen wir es Zugriffe auf verschiedene Applikations-Schichten im gleichen Testablauf zu ermöglichen?</p> <p>Weitere Herausforderungen liegen in der Integration des Test-Aufbaus in Abläufe der Continuous Integration:Mit dem vorgenannten Tooling haben wir die Möglichkeit unsere Test gut zu strukturieren und einzeln zu starten. Was aber wenn hunderte oder mehr Testfälle als \"Testset\" ausgeführt werden sollen?</p> <p>=&gt; Wie lässt sich das Tooling in nächtliche \"Build-Deploy-Test\" Abläufe integrieren mit Blick auf endliche Test-Laufzeit?</p> <p>Den Referenten des Abends - Björn Scherer - begleitet das Thema Testautomatisierung bereits seit mehr als zehn Jahren. Er arbeitet seit 2012 als Inhouse Test Consultant bei CosmosDirekt, und lebt hier agile Qualitätssicherung. Vor allem beschäftigt Björn sich mit den technischen Aspekten des Testen von Webanwendungen, sei dies die Umsetzung von Tests in Selenium, oder die Integration von Testautomatisierung in den Buildprozess. Vor seiner Arbeit bei CosmosDirekt hat Björn bei T-Systems gearbeitet und hier vor allem Erfahrung im Bereich des Lasttests gesammelt.</p> ','','',NULL),(45,2,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourg-Co-founders-Meetup/events/238050867/','<p>You have a neat idea. You are bursting with energy and creativity. You cannot get people to take you seriously because you are a one man show.  You simply cannot manage to stay on top of all that needs to be done to get your startup going.  You lack management/technical/marketing skills - pick your choice - and wish you could find people who might be able to fill those roles.  </p> <p>I have been there several times over - until I found my own cofounders about a year ago when I first started this group.  So why not join us for our next meetup and see what you can do if you find yourself in a similar predicament?  If you do not find your ideal cofounder(s) you will have had a pleasant time over a few drinks talking with a few kindred spirits.</p> <p><br/>The Big Beer Company is within <a href=\"https://www.google.lu/maps/dir/Place+d\">walking distance of Place d\'Armes</a>.  The No 9 and 14 buses ply the route at regular intervals with stops at Hamilius and rue des bains.</p> <p>I hope to see you there.</p> ','','',NULL),(46,2,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','https://www.meetup.com/Meditation-Yoga-Saarbrucken-Birkenfeld-Idar-Oberstein/events/238189764/','<p>Tous les mardis et jeudis à 19h</p> <p>140 Av. Gaston Diderich L-1420 Luxembourg</p> <p>Info : (00352)[masked] ou gsm (00352)[masked]</p> <p>or (00352)[masked] (also english spoken)</p> <p><br/>\"Dans le silence au-delà des pensées, vous trouvez la paix intérieure.\"<br/><a href=\"https://www.sahajayoga.be/fr/shri-mataji.html\">Shri Mataji Nirmala Devi</a></p> <p><b>Faites l\'expérience!</b></p> <p><b><br/></b></p> <p><a href=\"https://www.sahajayoga.be/fr/testimonials/celine.html\">\"La méditation donne véritablement un sens à ma vie, je me sens comme guidée vers ce qui est beau et juste.\"<br/></a><a href=\"https://www.sahajayoga.be/fr/testimonials/celine.html\">Celine, 39 ans,<br/>travailleur psycho-social</a></p> <p><a href=\"https://www.sahajayoga.be/fr/testimonials/celine.html\"><br/></a></p> <p><a href=\"https://www.sahajayoga.be/fr/luxembourg.html?lang=fr\" class=\"linkified\">https://www.sahajayoga.be/fr/luxembourg.html?lang=fr</a></p> <p>\n\n\nHello there! We\'d like to welcome you to our FREE weekly Sahaja Yoga meditation.</p> <p>With Sahaja Yoga Meditation we generally sit on chairs to achieve Yoga, effortlessly, spontaneously. As such no Asanas (exercises) are required, no mat or special clothing. We are all volunteers of a Charity organisation and have many years of experience in offering free Sahaja Yoga Meditation classes. The classes are designed to help those attending get into a genuine meditative state, which can be felt tangibly. It is quite effortless and spontaneous. The free classes feature introductory talks, video\'s, practical workshops and general question and answer opportunities, making them perfect for seekers trying to establish a state of yoga, and they are available throughout Luxembourg and  Germany.</p> <p>The idea is that you don\'t do yoga - you Achieve Yoga!</p> <p>Sahaja Yoga Meditation is a simple, time-honored technique. It helps those who enjoy it, reduce stress and increase wellness. It brings better focus and helps people become more centered and better balanced. Anyone can do it. Founded by Shri Mataji Nirmala Devi, Sahaja Yoga Meditation is a world wide movement for peace and self awakening.</p> <p>All the meetings and classes are free of any charge. Each week we go through simple meditation techniques, often with guided meditations to help reduce stress and achieve the peace of true meditation. We share tips on how to help stay in balance during the day and how to meditate at home. The meditation is based on connecting with the inner chakras (energy centres) and balancing the subtle body. The tradition and aims of meditation are explained which in essence is to be in the present with no mental activity or thoughts about the past or the future.</p> ','','',NULL),(47,2,NULL,'','2017-03-16 19:15:00','2017-03-16 21:45:00','','https://www.meetup.com/Spiritual-Network-Luxembourg/events/238196529/','','','',NULL),(48,2,NULL,'','2017-03-17 17:00:00','2017-03-17 20:00:00','','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourg-expats-and-repats/events/237426340/','','','',NULL),(49,2,NULL,'','2017-03-18 10:00:00','2017-03-18 12:00:00','','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourg-Badminton/events/238194761/','<p>Howdy! Players of the south of Luxembourg unite for a 2h session! The level of play is not important, but you must have a racket and know how to hold it =]</p> <p>Bring with you:</p> <p>1) Racket</p> <p>2) Indoor sport sneakers</p> <p>3) Smile</p> <p>The venue belongs to the local badminton club so come check it out for a first FREE session. If you think you would like to stay and play for the rest of the season talk with the coach about the rates, normally the member contribution is 100eur/year or 50eur/half-year.</p> <p>See you on the courts!</p> ','','',NULL),(50,2,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','https://www.meetup.com/hikes-with-dogs-in-luxembourg/events/238245346/','<p>Hi there,</p> <p>This is our next hike for dog owners and their dogs, as well as dog lovers. Everyone is welcome. The aim is to have a nice walk and chat while our dogs enjoy the woods.</p> <p>We are meeting at 10:30 at the <a href=\"https://goo.gl/maps/Q1jHgJEmJTn\">Aral gas station in Gonderange</a> and from there we are driving to the starting point at Rue de Gonderange between Bourglinster and Gonderange.</p> <p>Looking forward to seeing you!</p> ','','',NULL),(51,2,NULL,'','2017-03-18 11:00:00','2017-03-18 12:30:00','','https://www.meetup.com/coffeeclubluxembourg/events/238226231/','','','',NULL),(52,2,NULL,'','2017-03-18 15:00:00','2017-03-18 18:00:00','','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourg-Outdoors-Adventure-group/events/238289122/','','','',NULL),(53,2,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','https://www.meetup.com/B-loft/events/237449207/','<p>B:loft is pleased to announce a Slideshow Night event with Stephen Fabes, a London-based doctor, writer and adventurer. For six years, from 2010 to 2016, Stephen Fabes pedaled across 75 different countries, clocking up a distance of 86,209 km. From the war-struck deserts of Syria and Afghanistan to an outstandingly untoasty Mongolia mid-winter, Stephen Fabes dodged landslides and leaping camel spiders, was detained on suspicion of espionage in China, survived blizzards and tropical storms.</p> <p><b>Location: Rotondes<br/>Date: March 18<br/>Hours: 19:00 </b></p> <p>The event is designed not only for bicycle users, but also for adventure lovers (free entry). </p> <p>Following the presentation, Betty Buvette will serve a special menu inspired by Stephen Fabes’ cycling adventure. The menu will be a fusion of culinary traditions (dhaal à la noix de coco, falafel, som tum, naan bread). Tickets (€ 7+fee) are available at &lt;a&gt;www.rotondes.lu.&lt;/a&gt; </p> <p>After the delicious filling meal, B:loft invites you to a<b> night bike ride</b> in search of great panoramic views of Luxembourg-City. This will be a short and easy (ca. 4km), non-sportive urban bike ride suitable for everyone. We will cycle on bike paths or calm roads. The track will be revealed en route.</p> ','','',NULL),(54,2,NULL,'','2017-03-19 10:00:00','2017-03-31 13:00:00','','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourg-Culture-Group/events/235876111/','<p>LEAPA invites you to write. A play in English, that is. It can be of any performance length from ten minutes to an hour and a half, and either for stage production or, like Dylan Thomas’s Under Milk Wood, a play for voices to be performed without staging.</p> <p>We would like this competition and the selection of plays to be as objective as possible, so submission will be anonymous — see below. Once a play is selected, first by a LEAPA team and afterwards possibly at a LEAPA playreading, the author will be identified, contacted, and awarded a small prize. The aim is to find three final prizewinners, but there may be more if enough good entries are received.</p> <p>In 2018 New World Theatre Club will put on a third festival of short plays, particularly (but not exclusively) on the theme of WW1: minimum 10 minutes, maximum 15 minutes in performance. Any plays fitting those criteria and submitted for this LEAPA competition will also be considered by NWTC for inclusion in the festival. If you have a play that was submitted for, but not used in, a previous ten-minute play festival, please submit it again.</p> <p>But we are looking for longer plays as well. The emphasis will be on local writers. LEAPA will try to ensure that plays placed on the shortlist are either staged or read in public by a Luxembourg theatre group. They need not be completely new existing plays not yet staged will also be welcome, so long as they come from a local source or one with local connections.</p> <p>Please send play scripts ON PAPER to LEAPA at the address below by 31 March 2017, enclosing a sealed envelope containing your full contact details — name and address, telephone number and email address — and with the title of the play and its approximate performance length marked on the outside of the envelope. Please do not identify the author on the script itself. The inner envelope will be opened only after the play has been received, read and put to the vote.</p> <p><br/>Address for submission: </p> <p>LEAPA, 4 rue NS Pierret, L-2335 Luxembourg</p> <p><br/>Further details from [masked]</p> <p><a href=\"http://www.cercleculturel.lu/leapa/\"><a href=\"http://www.cercleculturel.lu/leapa/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.cercleculturel.lu/leapa/</a></a></p> <p><a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/leapa.luxembourg\">www.facebook.com/leapa.luxembourg</a></p> <p><a href=\"http://l.facebook.com/l.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nwtc.lu%2F&amp;h=EAQEGACCN&amp;enc=AZMnpKGHG5QOfK8Hh2Evw4_P3R-AJEYdfN-SyyQpt1ZA_XaJMxdXuVRXbUSQabo-T90&amp;s=1\">www.nwtc.lu</a></p> ','','',NULL),(55,2,NULL,'','2017-03-19 10:30:00','2017-03-19 13:00:00','','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourg-Ultimate-Frisbee/events/238289695/','<p>Come out for Sunday practices with the Luxembourg Ultimate frisbee team. Practices are informal (though we do drills and play games), and beginners are welcome! Even if only a few sign up through Meetup, practices still take place ! Send Thierry a mail through Meetup or Check our website for contact details ! More information here:  <a href=\"http://www.ultimate-delux.org/Main_Page#Practice\"><a href=\"http://www.ultimatedelux.org/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.ultimatedelux.org/</a></a></p> ','','',NULL),(56,2,NULL,'','2017-03-19 11:00:00','2017-03-19 17:00:00','','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourg-Outdoors-Adventure-group/events/238288457/','','','',NULL),(57,2,NULL,'','2017-03-19 11:30:00','2017-03-19 13:30:00','','https://www.meetup.com/coffeeclubluxembourg/events/238166342/','','','',NULL),(58,2,NULL,'','2017-03-19 13:00:00','2017-03-19 15:00:00','','https://www.meetup.com/metzfacesinternational/events/238236169/','','','',NULL),(59,2,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','https://www.meetup.com/Film-Fans-Lux/events/238320022/','','','',NULL),(60,2,NULL,'','2017-03-20 19:00:00','2017-03-20 21:00:00','','https://www.meetup.com/MICSE-Luxembourg-Professional-Development-Meetup/events/238165752/','<p>We\'ve invited two wonderful ladies - Anna Schmidt, a professional coach, and Victoria Byrum, a principal product manager at Microsoft - to talk about leadership and its attributes, if there are leadership skills and who is able to become a leader. Join us!</p> <p>Agenda:</p> <p>18:30 Doors open - welcome</p> <p>19:00 Discussion</p> <p>20:30 Networking</p> <p>Our speakers</p> <p><b>Anna Schmidt</b> is a certified coach of Goal Imagery Institute and has a diverse background including a diploma in marketing, a medical degree and PhD in Psychiatry. After several years of experience as a medical doctor in psychotherapy and psychiatry, she transitioned to the pharmaceutical industry, where she held various management and senior management positions in major pharma corporations such as Bayer and Merck with responsibilities including business development and operations in Ukraine. Since 2015, she has been an independent coach with a main focus on change management.</p> <p>Talking about the major success factor in her professional career, Mrs Schmidt has a simple and straightforward answer: “The continuous coaching and development of my direct reports and their teams. In business you cannot succeed alone, no matter how smart you are. You need highly motivated teams and attributes like trust and respect, which are key ingredients to any winning team. It is always surprising to see how so-called “average” team members self-transform once you help them realize what is blocking them, and when you coach them on how to overcome their self-imposed often-times unconscious barriers….  “ </p> <p><b>Victoria Byrum</b> is Principal Product Manager at Microsoft.<br/>She has spent 10 years in the tech industry, working in everything from marketing, to vendor management, to product management.</p> <p>Victoria is currently a Principal Product Manager for Microsoft here in Luxembourg, focused on delivering new experiences and revenue opportunities for Skype. Prior to joining Microsoft, she spent 8.5 years at Amazon, 6 of which were on the Kindle team where she ran the marketing team, product launches, and EU product strategy for Kindle e-readers and Fire TV in Europe. </p> <p>Victoria is American by birth (originally from NY), but Luxembourgish at heart (she has lived here over 6 years now, and truly loves it).  </p> <p>\n\n\nThanks go to Microsoft Luxembourg for kindly hosting this meeting.</p> <p>The number of places is limited.</p> <p><a href=\"http://www.facebook.com/micselu\">www.facebook.com/micselu</a> </p> ','','',NULL),(61,2,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourg-expats-and-repats/events/238239504/','','','',NULL),(62,2,NULL,'','2017-03-20 19:00:00','2017-03-20 21:00:00','','https://www.meetup.com/Innomate-Luxembourg-Innovation-and-Creativity-in-Business/events/238313054/','<p>It is always good to hear from other entrepreneurs about their own story.  It provides a valuable insight for those just starting out into the entrepreneurial arena.   To hear the good, the bad and the sometimes ugly parts of how an entrepreneur went through their own challenges provides information, support, motivation and tips for those just starting out, or perhaps to help those that are experiencing some difficulties along the way.</p> <p>We are pleased to welcome Bert Boerman of 2Gears for an interview with InnoMates Luxembourg, where we will hear about his own journey, the points that have led to the success of his business venture, the challenges faced and overcome and the points he may just have handled differently!</p> <p>Please join us for a relaxed chat with Bert, where you will also have an opportunity to put forward your own questions and network with the other members of the InnoMate Luxembourg Group.</p> ','','',NULL),(63,2,NULL,'','2017-03-21 16:15:00','2017-03-21 17:45:00','','https://www.meetup.com/Meetup-Bitcoins-Blockchains-Luxembourg/events/237997791/','<p>This meetup takes place in the 2nd floor of the Technoport. </p> <p><br/>Feel free to come to talk about bitcoin - blockchain. </p> <p><br/>Newbies or experts are welcomed as long as everyone may appear humble facing this revolution. </p> <p><br/>It\'s a monthly bitcoin - blockchain coffee break</p> ','','',NULL),(64,2,NULL,'','2017-03-21 19:00:00','2017-03-21 22:00:00','','https://www.meetup.com/PythonTrier/events/236315006/','<p>This is a meet for anyone interested in learning or tinkering with Python.  All experience levels are welcome. We meet on the second Tuesday or every month in the Machinendeck Hackerspace in Trier, so come on out!</p> ','','',NULL),(65,2,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','https://www.meetup.com/ReactJS-Luxembourg/events/237898779/','<p>This is our first meetup, the first of many to come. It would be super awesome if you can join us! Our goal is to bring together the React community, share knowledge and talk about anything related to the ecosystem.</p> <p>\n\n<b>SCHEDULE</b></p> <p><br/>- Opening<br/>- Introduction<br/>- First Talk: Keep calm and type check<br/>- Break<br/>- Second Talk: TBA<br/>- End</p> <p>Places are limited to 50 so please RSVP while you can!</p> <p><br/><i>Pizza and drinks will be provided :)</p> <p></i></p> <p><b>TALKS</b></p> <p><br/>- <b>Keep calm and type check</b>: Static type checking allows you to find bugs in your code before you run it, so you don\'t ship them to production. Flow-type is a static type checker for Javascript made by Facebook that will allow you to forget `undefined is not a function` for good. (by Gael du Plessix)</p> <p><br/>We still need a second talk, so please feel free to get in touch if you would like to give a talk.</p> ','','',NULL),(66,2,NULL,'','2017-03-21 19:00:00','2017-03-21 20:45:00','','https://www.meetup.com/The-inner-life-Transformation-from-inside-out/events/238054993/','<p>Hello everyone!</p> <p>I\'m looking forward to meet you all.</p> <p>I have a questionnaire to know you and to assess what you expect from this inner traveling experience. Its not very long, I promise ;). Please send me a message and I will send you the questionnaire. We can communicate here on meetup or by mail: [masked]</p> <p>Last thing...The days are getting bigger so I thought let\'s celebrate this fact with this amazing music...</p> <p>See you soon,</p> <p>Sandra</p> <p><a href=\"https://youtu.be/UubyV4ig_bw\" class=\"embedded\">https://youtu.be/UubyV4ig_bw</a></p> ','','',NULL),(67,2,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourg-expats-and-repats/events/238289903/','','','',NULL),(68,2,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','https://www.meetup.com/Meetup-API-Testing/events/238110839/','<p>Test Questions</p> ','','',NULL),(69,2,NULL,'','2017-03-22 20:00:00','2017-03-22 23:00:00','','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourgs-Indie-and-Alternative-Music-Meetup/events/238025253/','<p>Already the third social for 2017! Join us for a drink to talk about music, concerts and many other things.</p> ','','',NULL),(70,2,NULL,'','2017-03-23 18:00:00','2017-03-23 20:30:00','','https://www.meetup.com/luxembourginvestors/events/237582258/','','','',NULL),(71,2,NULL,'','2017-03-23 18:00:00','2017-03-25 18:00:00','','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourg-Agile-Human-Resource-Meetup/events/237723118/','<p>#play14 is an international gathering of like-minded people who share the common idea that playing is the best way to learn and understand !</p> <p>Tell me and I forget, teach me and I may remember, involve me and I learn.<br/>Benjamin Franklin<br/>For two and a half days, people with many different profiles and experiences are invited to share serious games &amp; fun activities, experiences &amp; tips, knowledge &amp; insights, laughts &amp; smiles. Everyone is welcome to join.</p> <p>Join us in order to develop your facilitation skills, increase your ability to accompany change in your organization, foster your creativity and improve your capacity to innovate.</p> <p>#play14 is an unconference, where all attendees are also contributors. All you need to do is show up, and you will be given the opportunity to propose some games, or play the games proposed by the others.</p> <p>Register here : <a href=\"http://play14.org/events/luxembourg/2017-03\" class=\"linkified\">http://play14.org/events/luxembourg/2017-03</a></p> ','','',NULL),(72,2,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','https://www.meetup.com/JEDI-Jeudi-Digital/events/238055049/','<p>Après avoir été accueilli chez Nyuko au Luxembourg le 16 février dernier, Grand Est Numérique organisera son premier After Work messin de l’année 2017 dans le cadre des JEDI (Jeudi Digitaux) le jeudi 23 mars à 18h à TCRM-Blida. Cet événement s’intègre dans une semaine particulièrement riche en terme de numérique ; effectivement, il aura lieu le soir du Startup Show 42 et la veille du Startup Weekend Metz qui se dérouleront dans les même locaux.</p> <p>Les objectifs des After Work :</p> <p>Développer l’écosystème du Grand Est afin que tous les acteurs (étudiants, privés, publics, salariés, dirigeants, freelances, etc.) qui proviennent de l’ensemble du tissu économique (écoles, startups, PME, TPE, grands groupes, institutions…etc.) puissent se rencontrer et échanger.<br/>Rencontrer et découvrir le maximum d’acteurs afin de connaître au mieux le tissu régional, les activités,les problématiques liées aux territoires et aux professions.<br/>Créer du business dans l’Est de la France et au Luxembourg, en tissant des liens solides avec l’ensemble de l’écosystème, le tout dans une ambiance convivial autour d’un verre.<br/>Le principe? Rien de bien compliqué !</p> <p>Inscrivez-vous<br/>Présentez-vous à l’entrée et recevez votre badge<br/>Ecoutez les mots de bienvenue par Grand Est Numérique et ses partenaires<br/>Échangez avec les acteurs présents (idéalement ce que vous ne connaissez pas encore).<br/>En même temps, découvrez les adhérents de l’association, grâce aux slides de présentation qui défileront sur l’écran dans la salle.<br/>Repartez d’une soirée conviviale en ayant découvert de nouveaux contacts.<br/>Donc, peu importe qui vous êtes, ce que vous faites ! Si vous vous intéressez au numérique, vous êtes le (et la) bienvenu(e) à Metz dans les locaux de TCRM-BLIDA le 23 mars.</p> <p>Pour ceux qui auraient manqué l’information, TCRM Blida c’est quoi ?</p> <p>TCRM-BLIDA c’est quoi ?</p> <p>Situé dans les anciens dépôts de bus de la ville de Metz, c’est aujourd’hui un Tiers-Lieu de création, de production et d’innovation artistique et numérique.En effet depuis sa création, le lieu parie sur l\'innovation croisée en faisant se côtoyer dans ses murs des artistes et de jeunes entrepreneurs de l\'économie numérique. Porté par le Pôle métropolitain européen du Sillon Lorrain, la candidature de LORnTECH au label \"Métropole French Tech\" a vu naturellement s\'imposer, TCRM-BLIDA, comme bâtiment totem pour la ville de Metz.</p> ','','',NULL),(73,2,NULL,'','2017-03-23 18:15:00','2017-03-23 20:30:00','','https://www.meetup.com/Luxembourg-Ultimate-Frisbee/events/238021395/','<p>Come out (or indoors!) for Thursday evening practices with the Luxembourg Ultimate frisbee team.  When indoor (Winter), we meet at Lycee Aline Mayrisch: Parallel to the Blvd Pierre Dupond is a red running track, go up the stairs and you will see the indoor gym. If outdoor (Spring/Summer/Fall), we meet either at Michel Lucius in Limpertsberg or the ISL artificial turf field (International School Lux in Hollerich), right behind the same red track, in the ISL campus. Meetup will be updated with the venue.</p> <p><br/>Practices are open to All, free while you discover the game and team, and Beginners are welcome ! We stretch and warm up, do drills, work strategy and play games. Even if only a few sign up through Meetup, practices still take place ! Send Thierry a mail through Meetup or Check our website for contact details ! More information here:  <a href=\"http://www.ultimate-delux.org/Main_Page#Practice\"><a href=\"http://www.ultimatedelux.org/\" class=\"linkified\">http://www.ultimatedelux.org/</a></a></p> ','','',NULL),(74,2,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,'','https://www.meet